        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 17 at 9:58PM MDT until July 17 at 10:30PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 957 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Nashua, or 11
miles east of Glasgow, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Nashua, Fort Peck, Fort Peck Marina, Frazer, Duck Creek Rec Area,
Rock Creek Rec Area, Park Grove, and Whatley.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
